SOAP / REST

Api gateway

component-2 - Java

POSTMAN

Component of APIs (REST)

1 - Host + Endpoint
2 - Headers - Auth, content-type
3 - CRUD - Create (POST) ,Read(GET) , Update (PUT (complete resource) AND PATCH(partial resource) ) and Delete (DELETE)
4 - Payload - JSON, HTML, TXT

Response
Code

1XX = Information
2XX = Success
    200 = OK
    201 = create
    204 = no-content
3XX = Redirectional
    300 = multiple choice
    301 = moved permanantly

4XX = client
    400 = Bad Request
    401 = Auth issue
    403 = forbidden
    404 = resource not found
    405 = Method not allowed

5XX = server - raise a bug
    500 = internal server error
    502
    503 = service not available

Xpath

JSONPath =

{
name : "Vaibhav",
age : 34
}
String firstname = jsonpath("name");
int age = jsonpath("age")
